# Mobile App Remediation Plan (iOS & Android)

## ðŸš¨ Critical Priority: Layout & Safe Area
The primary goal is to resolve the "Dynamic Island" and Notch obstruction issues across **ALL** views, not just the landing page.

- [x] **Global Application Wrapper Fix**
  - Implement a `pt-[env(safe-area-inset-top)]` redundancy at the `App.tsx` or `Layout.tsx` level to force content down globally on native devices.
  - Ensure `viewport-fit=cover` is working (verified).
  - **Task**: Modify `client/index.css` or `Layout.tsx` to handle `capacitor-platform-ios` specific classes. (DONE: Added global CSS rule)

- [x] **Technician & Dashboard Headers**
  - The "My Jobs / Select Client" header (seen in screenshots) is currently crashing into the notch.
  - **Task**: Locate the component (likely `JobBoard.tsx`, `TechDashboard.tsx`, or a generic `PageHeader` component) and apply the same `isNative` padding logic used in the main Header.
  - **Fix**: Add `pt-16` or `pt-safe-offset` to these internal headers. (DONE: JobBoard.tsx updated with 60px padding)

- [ ] **Authentication Screens (Login/Signup)**
  - Ensure the "Welcome Back" container starts *below* the header/notch area.
  - **Task**: Check `SignIn.tsx` and `SignUp.tsx` specific layouts.

## ðŸ“± Mobile UX Polish
- [ ] **Touch Targets**: Ensure all buttons (especially "Back" arrows and Menu icons) are at least 44x44px.
- [ ] **Dual-Row Header Refinement**: Verify the new "Logo Top / Actions Bottom" layout feels natural and doesn't consume too much vertical space on smaller screens.
- [x] **Input/Select Zoom**: Updated `Select` and `Textarea` components to use `text-base` (16px) on mobile to prevent iOS auto-zoom on focus.
- [ ] **Keyboard Avoidance**: Ensure input fields (email/password) scroll into view when the keyboard opens (Capacitor Keyboard plugin config).

